features: A TREAT FOR AUDIOPHILES: KENWOOD KFC-6966R 6"x9" Road Series 3-Way coaxial car speakers with 400W peak power, 4-ohm impedance, cloth woofer cones, electro-dynamic tweeters, and sharp-looking grilles ensure high quality music that sounds like the original

POWER UP YOUR CAR AUDIO: These car coaxial speakers feature a nominal power of 45W RMS and a 35Hz - 20kHz frequency response, that deliver pristine highs, deep lows, and powerful bass, without compromising sound quality or experiencing any distortion

SOPHISTICATED SOUND: For an incredible boost in performance and exceptional sound quality, the KFC-6966R features a 4-ohm impedance, which conducts power evenly to keep the speakers at an appropriate level. They can be used as front or rear speakers

EASY TO INSTALL: These car audio speakers feature a heavy duty magnet design with lower tweeter heights and a shallow depth for easy installation and durability. The speakers have grilles for protection and are a perfect addition to your car audio system

body.description: Upgrade your car sound system by adding the KENWOOD KFC-6966R 6"x9" Road Series 3-way car speaker set - a pair of coaxial speakers that deliver exceptional sound quality with rich bass. Features polypropylene cloth woofers and electro-dynamic tweeters that improve sensitivity while reducing distortion for accurate highs and deep lows. With the standard 4-ohm impedance and 35Hz-20kHz frequency response, these 6x9 car speakers ensure that your music sounds like the original. These KENWOOD speakers are efficient to work with your car radio or an amplifier with a nominal power RMS of 45W. The speakers can handle a peak power of 400W without a deflection in sound quality. Say goodbye to the mediocre sound of regular factory speakers and add the KFC-6966R speakers to your car's music system to achieve significantly better sound quality and booming performance.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 21, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Cheap easy upgrade
reviews.reviewText: These speakers were an excellent inexpensive upgrade for my daughter's 07 charger. Her right front speaker was blown. These were priced right and sound great. It should be noted, however, that they are not a simple drop in. I had to cut some of the baffling away from the door inserts. Wasn't a big deal, and a good utility knife got it done in a couple of minutes. Just be advised you'll have to do that small modification, simply because the speakers are a little beefier than the stock six by nines. You may also want to pick up some wiring adapters specific for your vehicle, if you're not comfortable with doing wiring work. I simply cut off the stock adapters and put spade clips on the wires and connect them directly to the speakers. You can then just crimp them tight, or put a drop of solder on to be safe.
